00:00:22,690 --> 00:00:23,691
<i>A long time ago,</i>

4
00:00:25,568 --> 00:00:30,197
<i>there lived a beautiful girl in a castle
located deep inside the forest.</i>

5
00:00:34,910 --> 00:00:37,079
<i>She was always alone,
so she was lonely and bored.</i>

6
00:00:38,330 --> 00:00:42,167
<i>So one day, she left the castle
to find herself a friend to play with.</i>

7
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:48,799
<i>She offered them
all sorts of amazing gifts,</i>

8
00:00:49,425 --> 00:00:51,093
<i>but nobody ever accepted her.</i>

9
00:00:52,928 --> 00:00:55,723
<i>Later on, she found out why.</i>

10
00:00:57,182 --> 00:00:59,310
<i>A monster who brings along
the shadow of death.</i>

11
00:01:00,019 --> 00:01:01,645
<i>That's what the people called her.</i>

12
00:01:02,980 --> 00:01:05,149
<i>"She's a monster. A monster."</i>

13
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:12,072
<i>She was very angry
at every living soul in the world.</i>

14
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:14,950
<i>And she needed to take it out on someone.</i>

15
00:01:48,692 --> 00:01:52,863
<i>Ever since she had unexpectedly
saved the boy from dying,</i>

16
00:01:54,031 --> 00:01:58,452
<i>the scary shadow that always
followed her around suddenly disappeared.</i>

17
00:02:01,664 --> 00:02:05,084
<i>And the boy always
followed her around instead.</i>

18
00:02:06,502 --> 00:02:09,588
<i>He always went with her
whether it was day or night</i>

19
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:12,591
<i>and whether she was in the mountains
or on a field.</i>

20
00:02:15,761 --> 00:02:18,639
<i>On a clear and sunny day,
the girl asked him this.</i>

21
00:02:19,348 --> 00:02:23,102
<i>"Hey, will you always stay by my side?"</i>

22
00:02:24,061 --> 00:02:26,647
<i>"Of course. I will never run away."</i>

23
00:02:28,649 --> 00:02:30,067
<i>"Even after you see this?"</i>

24
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:47,751
<i>The girl was all alone again,</i>

25
00:02:48,127 --> 00:02:50,963
<i>and that's when the shadow of death
came back and whispered this.</i>

26
00:02:53,924 --> 00:02:56,427
<i>"No one can ever stay by your side</i>

27
00:02:57,761 --> 00:03:01,306
<i>because you're a monster.</i>

28
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:06,520
<i>Do not ever forget that.
Do you understand?"</i>

29
00:03:07,730 --> 00:03:10,190
Yes, Mother.

30
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:20,200
<font color="#ffff80">CHAPTER 1 THE BOY WHO FED ON NIGHTMARES</font>

31
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:24,037
<font color="#ffff80"><i> THE BOY WHO FED ON NIGHTMARES</i></font>

32
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:32,713
<i>This stop is Daun Vocational School.</i>

33
00:03:33,297 --> 00:03:35,758
<i>The next stop is...</i>

34
00:03:43,849 --> 00:03:47,311
<i>I mean, he threw a huge fit
in the middle of class.</i>

35
00:03:47,394 --> 00:03:48,729
<i>My goodness.</i>

36
00:03:49,146 --> 00:03:50,439
No!

37
00:03:57,279 --> 00:03:58,947
There's no use in trying to stop him.

38
00:03:59,031 --> 00:04:01,158
And this isn't the first time.

39
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:02,659
<i>Your expression shows your emotions</i>

40
00:04:02,743 --> 00:04:04,995
What if there was a dangerous tool
right next to him?

41
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:06,747
It would've led to an accident.

42
00:04:16,632 --> 00:04:19,426
I don't understand
why we always need to walk on eggshells

43
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:21,386
-because of Sang-tae.
-Is he angry?

44
00:04:21,470 --> 00:04:22,721
Is he angry?

45
00:04:24,306 --> 00:04:26,183
-Anyway, we need to think of safety,
-Angry...

46
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:28,310
-Getting annoyed.
-and he's too much for us to handle.

47
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:32,689
Just send him to a special needs school
or a local community center.

48
00:04:32,773 --> 00:04:34,900
That will be best for everyone.

49
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:38,237
-<i>Your expression shows your emotions</i>
-Tell me what you think.

50
00:04:38,654 --> 00:04:39,613
What do you think?

51
00:04:40,197 --> 00:04:42,658
Will you please say something?
My gosh, seriously.

52
00:04:58,799 --> 00:05:00,217
He's angry.

53
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,052
<font color="#ffff80"><i> THE BOY WHO FED ON NIGHTMARES</i></font>

54
00:05:24,366 --> 00:05:25,576
<font color="#ffff80">MOON SANG-TAE</font>

55
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,344
Sang-tae.

56
00:05:46,555 --> 00:05:47,806
Aren't you hungry?

57
00:05:53,979 --> 00:05:55,355
What do you want to eat?

58
00:05:59,318 --> 00:06:01,403
You weren't planning to stay here
for that long anyway.

59
00:06:04,531 --> 00:06:06,867
I'll find you a better school
once we move.

60
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:07,993
I promise.

61
00:06:13,707 --> 00:06:15,375
-Are you that upset?
-<i>Jjamppong.</i>

62
00:06:15,542 --> 00:06:17,502
-What?
-<i>Tangsuyuk</i> with sauce on the side.

63
00:06:17,586 --> 00:06:20,756
Let's not go to Jageumseong.
Let's eat at Yangjagang.

64
00:06:22,174 --> 00:06:25,135
Okay, let's stuff ourselves with food
at Yangjagang.

65
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:27,095
The food is really good there.
Do you remember?

66
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:31,016
When was the last time we went?

67
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:33,226
Don't worry. I'll buy.
I'm your big brother.

68
00:07:37,499 --> 00:07:40,127
By any chance, are you
Author Ko Mun-yeong?

69
00:07:41,503 --> 00:07:43,463
-Yes.
-See? I told you.

70
00:07:44,506 --> 00:07:47,217
My daughter is a big fan of yours.

71
00:07:47,634 --> 00:07:49,052
I'm sorry to ask this,

72
00:07:50,971 --> 00:07:52,806
but can we please get your autograph?

73
00:08:00,439 --> 00:08:02,858
-Your name?
-Lee Seul-bi.

74
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:06,486
She's really beautiful in real life,
isn't she?

75
00:08:06,570 --> 00:08:10,282
Yes, she's like a princess
from a fairy tale.

76
00:08:18,081 --> 00:08:20,751
-Why do you think I'm like a princess?
-Because you're pretty.

77
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:24,713
My mom always calls me "princess"

78
00:08:24,796 --> 00:08:26,089
because I'm pretty.

79
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:32,888
Ma'am, how about a photo?

80
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:34,556
My goodness, thank you.

81
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,183
Go stand next to her.

82
00:08:37,976 --> 00:08:38,935
Come here.

83
00:08:43,899 --> 00:08:46,610
You're not my fan, are you?

84
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:49,362
Pardon?

85
00:08:49,863 --> 00:08:53,408
In all my fairy tales,
the witch is always the one that's pretty.

86
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:58,080
Who told you all princesses
are kind and pretty?

87
00:08:58,872 --> 00:09:00,248
Did your mom tell you that?

88
00:09:00,332 --> 00:09:02,876
Princess, look over here.

89
00:09:03,502 --> 00:09:06,671
If you really want to be that pretty,
I want you to say this.

90
00:09:07,172 --> 00:09:09,466
-One.
-"Mom.

91
00:09:10,509 --> 00:09:12,552
-I'm going to be...
-Two.

92
00:09:13,303 --> 00:09:16,306
a pretty witch."

93
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:17,724
Three.

94
00:09:24,439 --> 00:09:25,440
Princess.

95
00:09:25,524 --> 00:09:28,443
-Oh, goodness.
-Princess!

96
00:09:30,529 --> 00:09:31,988
My gosh.

97
00:09:35,367 --> 00:09:36,618
My gosh. Mun-yeong.

98
00:09:40,622 --> 00:09:42,249
<i>Buongiorno</i>, Mun-yeong.

99
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:45,961
My gosh, what's with this chain?

100
00:09:48,547 --> 00:09:51,258
What made that little kid cry her eyes out
so early in the morning?

101
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:54,219
I guess she was touched.
I helped her correct her misconception.

102
00:09:55,303 --> 00:09:56,138
What in the world...

103
00:09:59,099 --> 00:10:00,225
Good job.

104
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:04,354
It can be very dangerous
for a kid to be biased towards something.

105
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:06,064
But you helped her fix that?

106
00:10:06,773 --> 00:10:09,693
You really are amazing, Mun-yeong.

107
00:10:10,402 --> 00:10:11,403
Just a second.

108
00:10:14,364 --> 00:10:15,282
<font color="#ffff80">OK PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL</font>

109
00:10:15,365 --> 00:10:17,492
I don't need your loan. I'm already rich.

110
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:22,789
Okay, let's get going.

111
00:10:22,873 --> 00:10:24,583
We have about two hours.

112
00:10:24,666 --> 00:10:26,585
So you have time to go to a beauty salon.

113
00:10:26,877 --> 00:10:27,711
Why would I go there?

114
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:31,464
You can't go there looking like that.

115
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:35,385
You look like Francesca
who is on her way to a funeral

116
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:37,804
for the Addams Family.

117
00:10:37,888 --> 00:10:40,265
You can't go to a children's ward
looking like that.

118
00:10:40,765 --> 00:10:44,394
You're not going there to scare the kids.
You're going there to give them hope.

119
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:46,146
You'll be reading your fairy tale there.

120
00:10:46,229 --> 00:10:48,982
-But you look--
-You said it's dangerous to be biased.

121
00:10:49,566 --> 00:10:51,484
I personally think you're more dangerous.

122
00:10:52,611 --> 00:10:55,071
Mun-yeong, please.

123
00:10:55,155 --> 00:10:57,032
You should dress according to the TPO.

124
00:11:03,955 --> 00:11:06,207
I'll tell them to come to you.

125
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:11,046
Do you know why I like this restaurant?

126
00:11:12,005 --> 00:11:15,008
-Because the steak--
-No.

127
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:18,386
The knife here

128
00:11:19,346 --> 00:11:21,014
is amazing.

129
00:11:23,558 --> 00:11:25,518
-Look.
-Mun-yeong, you're bleeding.

130
00:11:27,479 --> 00:11:28,730
How pretty.

131
00:11:30,815 --> 00:11:31,858
I want it.

132
00:11:36,071 --> 00:11:37,989
Good gracious.

133
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:41,451
Ma'am.

134
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:44,496
Just a second.

135
00:12:17,112 --> 00:12:18,530
<font color="#ffff80">EMPLOYEE CARD CAREGIVER MOON GANG-TAE</font>

136
00:12:20,323 --> 00:12:22,075
Mr. Moon, you need to come to the lounge.

137
00:12:27,706 --> 00:12:31,626
Gosh, that thief ate all my food.

138
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:33,753
It's as if she's been starving for days.

139
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:44,264
Ms. Myoung Ji-suk.

140
00:12:47,892 --> 00:12:48,727
Honey.

141
00:12:57,402 --> 00:12:58,862
I feel so empty.

142
00:12:59,863 --> 00:13:02,365
Even so,
you shouldn't eat in such a hurry.

143
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:04,617
If you do,
you'll get an upset stomach again.

144
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:07,746
So don't eat everything all at once.

145
00:13:09,247 --> 00:13:11,458
Instead, it'd be great
if you could take your time

146
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,586
to eat your food.

147
00:13:15,170 --> 00:13:16,921
You told me you liked that I ate well.

148
00:13:18,590 --> 00:13:20,633
You took it the wrong way.

149
00:13:20,717 --> 00:13:24,262
It's just that when you like someone,
you even like the way they eat.

150
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:29,601
Honey.

151
00:13:32,729 --> 00:13:33,772
Then

152
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:40,236
why did you cheat on me
with that skinny model?

153
00:14:34,666 --> 00:14:35,792
It's okay.

154
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:39,170
Don't smile at me.

155
00:14:40,338 --> 00:14:41,506
It disgusts me.

156
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:48,471
-Put your arms up like this.
-Let me go!

157
00:14:48,555 --> 00:14:50,682
Then pull them down like this.

158
00:14:51,182 --> 00:14:52,767
-Stay still!
-I don't belong here!

159
00:14:52,851 --> 00:14:55,520
Let me go! Let go of me!

160
00:14:55,603 --> 00:14:57,564
I can't go in here! I can't!

161
00:14:57,814 --> 00:14:59,190
Let go!

162
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:01,025
I don't belong here!

163
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:02,735
-Is he a new patient?
-Let me go!

164
00:15:02,819 --> 00:15:05,155
Two days ago, he overdosed
on alprazolam with his daughter

165
00:15:05,238 --> 00:15:06,531
and came as an emergency patient.

166
00:15:06,614 --> 00:15:09,242
He used to get treated
for his anxiety disorder.

167
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:11,327
I think he tried
to commit suicide with her.

168
00:15:11,536 --> 00:15:14,956
By the looks of it, I think he wanted to
kill his daughter and then kill himself.

169
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:16,040
Where's Go-eun?

170
00:15:16,124 --> 00:15:19,544
Where is Go-eun? Where is my daughter?

171
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:22,213
<i>Fortunately, she threw up
right after she took the drug.</i>

172
00:15:22,297 --> 00:15:25,967
<i>And she's getting counseling for PTSD
at our child psychology department.</i>

173
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:27,594
Go-eun.

174
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:30,180
Go-eun, what's on your mind?

175
00:15:31,890 --> 00:15:33,266
<i>Let me go!</i>

176
00:15:33,349 --> 00:15:36,019
He's going to receive
a psychiatric assessment this afternoon.

177
00:15:36,102 --> 00:15:37,645
So check his vitals every hour.

178
00:15:37,729 --> 00:15:40,940
And double-check the restraining band
as you give him an IV fluid.

179
00:15:41,524 --> 00:15:42,442
Okay.

180
00:15:43,193 --> 00:15:45,403
After the reading, you will
answer questions from the audience.

181
00:15:45,486 --> 00:15:48,865
Then you'll give out
your autographed storybooks to the kids.

182
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:52,577
And you'll be done once you take a photo
with the hospital staff for PR.

183
00:15:56,039 --> 00:15:59,542
I'm not sure if I'm a secretary
or the CEO of a publishing company.

184
00:16:00,126 --> 00:16:01,502
I'm seriously starting to wonder.

185
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:04,672
I got hired as an art director.

186
00:16:04,756 --> 00:16:08,801
But I had no idea that I'd be
working as your minion.

187
00:16:08,885 --> 00:16:11,137
Hey, you told me you'll do anything
during the interview.

188
00:16:11,221 --> 00:16:15,642
Well, I didn't know
you'd make me do physical labor.

189
00:16:15,725 --> 00:16:18,186
I hired you
knowing that you're not very smart.

190
00:16:18,269 --> 00:16:20,813
What do you want me to do?
Should I just fire you?

191
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:21,814
No.

192
00:16:25,026 --> 00:16:26,486
<font color="#ffff80">OK PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL</font>

193
00:16:28,029 --> 00:16:29,405
“OK Psychiatric Hospital”?

194
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:31,991
Sir, do you get counseling?

195
00:16:32,617 --> 00:16:34,536
That's such a good idea.

196
00:16:36,538 --> 00:16:37,997
Answer the phone.

197
00:16:43,044 --> 00:16:45,171
-Hello?
-Put it on speaker.

198
00:16:48,091 --> 00:16:50,677
<i>Hello? Mr. Lee?</i>

199
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:54,389
<i>I'm Nam Ju-ri,
a nurse at OK Psychiatric Hospital.</i>

200
00:16:54,764 --> 00:16:55,974
Come this way.

201
00:16:56,474 --> 00:16:59,644
It's so hard to reach you.
You never text us back either.

202
00:17:01,479 --> 00:17:02,814
Are you listening?

203
00:17:03,314 --> 00:17:06,317
Oh, yes. I'm a bit busy--

204
00:17:06,401 --> 00:17:07,652
<i>I believe we told you</i>

205
00:17:08,236 --> 00:17:10,446
that we set a date
for Mr. Ko Dae-hwan's surgery.

206
00:17:13,574 --> 00:17:15,410
How long do we need to wait

207
00:17:16,661 --> 00:17:18,121
for the guardian's consent?

208
00:17:19,122 --> 00:17:21,624
You can't keep
avoiding our calls like this.

209
00:17:23,084 --> 00:17:25,086
That's the same thing
as killing the patient.

210
00:17:25,962 --> 00:17:27,046
Ko Dae-hwan.

211
00:17:28,548 --> 00:17:30,216
He's dead to me.

212
00:17:31,384 --> 00:17:34,470
Why do you keep trying to bring him back
to life? Are you Jesus?

213
00:17:35,263 --> 00:17:36,556
-Excuse me.
-<i>Ju-ri.</i>

214
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:40,476
If you're so desperate,
come and get the signature yourself.

215
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:04,500
What's wrong? What is it?

216
00:18:05,001 --> 00:18:07,754
-What happened?
-She wants me to go to her.

217
00:18:09,255 --> 00:18:10,757
Is she out of her mind or what?

218
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:12,967
If she's not sane, she should come here.

219
00:18:13,343 --> 00:18:14,427
Ms. Park.

220
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:16,971
Let me hear about his medical history.

221
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,769
The patient in room 203 with dementia.

222
00:18:22,852 --> 00:18:23,686
Oh, Mr. Ko Dae-hwan?

223
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:28,232
He needs to get surgery
due to his glioblastoma relapse.

224
00:18:28,316 --> 00:18:29,776
But his guardian doesn't care?

225
00:18:30,693 --> 00:18:33,279
This patient has been with us
for the longest period of time.

226
00:18:33,363 --> 00:18:36,783
But his guardian
never once visited or called

227
00:18:36,866 --> 00:18:39,035
which means he's being neglected.

228
00:18:39,744 --> 00:18:43,206
So instead of just
calling his ungrateful guardian,

229
00:18:43,289 --> 00:18:45,375
why don't you actually visit her in person

230
00:18:45,458 --> 00:18:47,668
so that we can save the patient?

231
00:18:47,752 --> 00:18:48,961
What?

232
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:52,006
Is that really necessary?

233
00:18:52,090 --> 00:18:55,385
You're going to do it, right?
I know you're a professional.

234
00:18:56,969 --> 00:18:59,847
If you let me take the rest of the day
and tomorrow off,

235
00:19:00,723 --> 00:19:02,684
-I'll go see her myself.
-Why do you need two days?

236
00:19:03,309 --> 00:19:05,269
Do you have a boyfriend in Seoul?

237
00:19:07,021 --> 00:19:08,147
I guess you do.

238
00:19:08,231 --> 00:19:10,983
Ju-ri, you have a boyfriend?

239
00:19:11,901 --> 00:19:12,735
No.

240
00:19:12,819 --> 00:19:15,571
Well then, I'll be off soon.

241
00:19:18,533 --> 00:19:20,660
I bet she does have a boyfriend.

242
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:22,578
She's a traitor.

243
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:54,277
I don't think your daughter
