490
00:37:34,994 --> 00:37:37,830
In this world,
there are people who deserve to die.

491
00:37:38,748 --> 00:37:40,875
But some thoughtful freaks

492
00:37:40,958 --> 00:37:43,461
kill them for us in secret.

493
00:37:44,212 --> 00:37:47,632
That is why the clueless civilians
can sleep peacefully at night,

494
00:37:48,549 --> 00:37:50,051
completely unaware of it.

495
00:37:54,055 --> 00:37:55,640
Which one do you think I am?

496
00:38:09,195 --> 00:38:10,404
You're

497
00:38:11,948 --> 00:38:12,782
a clueless freak.

498
00:38:27,088 --> 00:38:28,714
Oh, boy.

499
00:38:29,257 --> 00:38:32,301
Thanks to you, my suturing skills
are getting better by the day.

500
00:38:33,970 --> 00:38:36,556
Stop hurting yourself already.

501
00:38:41,269 --> 00:38:42,311
Mr. Moon?

502
00:38:43,646 --> 00:38:44,855
Mr. Moon Gang-tae.

503
00:38:46,148 --> 00:38:47,149
Yes?

504
00:38:47,900 --> 00:38:49,235
What were you thinking about?

505
00:38:53,030 --> 00:38:53,948
It's done.

506
00:38:54,865 --> 00:38:57,368
Okay, fine.
The event turned into total chaos

507
00:38:57,451 --> 00:39:00,663
because of the patient who escaped,
so let's just consider it buzz marketing.

508
00:39:00,746 --> 00:39:03,499
But what about the knife fight?
How are you going to explain it?

509
00:39:03,708 --> 00:39:05,751
You said one of the hospital staff
got hurt.

510
00:39:05,835 --> 00:39:07,795
What if they distribute a press release?

511
00:39:08,087 --> 00:39:10,214
"A famous children's book author
brandished a knife.

512
00:39:10,298 --> 00:39:14,218
Is she working on a martial arts novel?"
You'll see the headlines everywhere.

513
00:39:14,302 --> 00:39:16,053
Just bribe them.
You've done it many times.

514
00:39:16,345 --> 00:39:18,222
What if that doesn't work? What do we do?

515
00:39:18,306 --> 00:39:19,974
We'll use a honey trap. I'll seduce them.

516
00:39:27,315 --> 00:39:28,357
Get in.

517
00:39:31,694 --> 00:39:33,696
You go ahead.
I have to take care of something.

518
00:39:34,447 --> 00:39:35,948
What do you need to do?

519
00:39:37,450 --> 00:39:38,784
Hey, Mun-yeong!

520
00:39:39,285 --> 00:39:41,329
Is she going to cause trouble again?

521
00:39:41,871 --> 00:39:42,705
<font color="#ffff80">ADMIN MANAGER</font>

522
00:39:42,788 --> 00:39:44,874
A patient who should have been
in solitary confinement

523
00:39:45,583 --> 00:39:47,376
barged in there and ruined the event.

524
00:39:48,294 --> 00:39:51,756
The guardians are calling to complain,
so the phones are ringing off the hook.

525
00:39:52,423 --> 00:39:56,093
We need to quickly find someone
who will take the bullet.

526
00:39:58,554 --> 00:40:00,973
Are you saying I should be that person?

527
00:40:01,557 --> 00:40:04,018
The one who was in charge
of the transfer is a newbie,

528
00:40:04,602 --> 00:40:06,479
so I can't really fire him.

529
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:09,482
I see here that you've worked

530
00:40:10,066 --> 00:40:13,319
at so many different hospitals
in the past ten years.

531
00:40:13,527 --> 00:40:15,988
My gosh, 15 hospitals in total.

532
00:40:17,031 --> 00:40:18,741
And less than a year at all of them.

533
00:40:18,949 --> 00:40:20,451
You've been with us for ten months now,

534
00:40:21,660 --> 00:40:24,121
<i>so you'll be quitting soon anyway.</i>

535
00:40:24,205 --> 00:40:25,331
<font color="#ffff80">EMPLOYEE CARD CAREGIVER MOON GANG-TAE</font>

536
00:40:28,668 --> 00:40:29,835
Gang-tae.

537
00:40:33,005 --> 00:40:36,050
<i>I'll say you worked here for a year
so that you can get your severance pay.</i>

538
00:40:37,051 --> 00:40:38,427
<i>Let's just sort it out like that.</i>

539
00:40:55,778 --> 00:40:57,279
Hey, it's me.

540
00:40:57,905 --> 00:41:01,242
Get me the contact information of the guy
who got hurt because of Mun-yeong.

541
00:41:02,118 --> 00:41:03,494
What do you think?

542
00:41:03,744 --> 00:41:05,955
I need to bribe him or something
to silence him.

543
00:41:06,205 --> 00:41:07,456
Come on. You know the drill.

544
00:41:41,574 --> 00:41:43,284
<font color="#ffff80">JAE-SU'S FRIED CHICKEN DELIVERY</font>

545
00:41:51,834 --> 00:41:53,085
I was delivering an order

546
00:41:53,210 --> 00:41:55,087
but saw a guy sitting here
looking like a sick chicken

547
00:41:55,171 --> 00:41:56,464
and knew it was you.

548
00:42:04,096 --> 00:42:05,598
Hop on. I'll give you a ride.

549
00:42:07,433 --> 00:42:08,517
You freak.

550
00:42:11,437 --> 00:42:12,855
You hurt yourself again?

551
00:42:31,499 --> 00:42:33,209
Damn it.

552
00:42:34,418 --> 00:42:36,003
Is he ignoring my calls?

553
00:42:37,713 --> 00:42:41,091
If he bled, I'm sure he'll sue her.

554
00:42:42,384 --> 00:42:44,512
<font color="#ffff80">NURSE NAM JU-RI</font>

555
00:42:48,682 --> 00:42:50,142
Hello, Ms. Nam.

556
00:42:50,976 --> 00:42:53,187
Oh, I see. You're already here?

557
00:42:54,563 --> 00:42:55,606
Right.

558
00:42:56,357 --> 00:42:58,192
The room number is...

559
00:43:00,778 --> 00:43:01,820
Just a moment, please.

560
00:43:09,495 --> 00:43:10,955
Did you order room service?

561
00:43:17,002 --> 00:43:18,796
Where did he go?

562
00:44:10,222 --> 00:44:11,223
Thanks.

563
00:44:18,897 --> 00:44:21,191
Alberto, no. Don't do this to me.

564
00:44:21,275 --> 00:44:23,360
No, Alberto. Don't be like this.
Please, Alberto!

565
00:44:23,444 --> 00:44:25,613
No! Don't do this to me, Alberto!

566
00:44:25,821 --> 00:44:27,156
-Shit.
-What's wrong?

567
00:44:27,239 --> 00:44:28,324
-Gosh!
-What's going on?

568
00:44:28,407 --> 00:44:30,743
Hang on. Alberto... Gosh!

569
00:44:32,745 --> 00:44:34,538
Alberto!

570
00:44:37,041 --> 00:44:38,542
Giddy-up!

571
00:44:38,626 --> 00:44:40,919
Alberto! Shit. Alberto, please...

572
00:44:42,212 --> 00:44:43,047
Don't die.

573
00:44:46,300 --> 00:44:47,259
Gang-tae!

574
00:44:48,719 --> 00:44:50,137
I'm really okay.

575
00:44:50,596 --> 00:44:53,515
Your brother must be waiting for you,
so just take a cab home!

576
00:44:54,683 --> 00:44:56,477
I won't say that you ditched me!

577
00:44:57,353 --> 00:44:58,395
I totally understand!

578
00:44:58,979 --> 00:45:02,107
Because that is
what a true loyal friend would do!

579
00:45:02,650 --> 00:45:04,276
Shut it and just keep on pulling.

580
00:45:07,946 --> 00:45:12,242
<font color="#ffff80">ANOTHER LONG DAY, RIGHT? CHEER UP!</font>

581
00:45:12,326 --> 00:45:15,204
<font color="#ffff80">YOU WILL MEET YOUR SOUL MATE SOON.</font>

582
00:45:35,932 --> 00:45:37,434
You've changed so much.

583
00:45:38,143 --> 00:45:41,146
I almost couldn't recognize you
because you no longer look like a hick.

584
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:46,484
Has it been almost 20 years
since I transferred to a different school?

585
00:45:47,903 --> 00:45:48,904
Yes.

586
00:45:50,739 --> 00:45:53,575
We just need your signature here.

587
00:45:54,075 --> 00:45:56,786
The doctor must've already
explained everything over the phone.

588
00:45:57,579 --> 00:45:59,456
You should actually do this in person--

589
00:45:59,539 --> 00:46:03,168
Hey, you traveled for three hours

590
00:46:03,251 --> 00:46:05,170
just to get my signature
on this stupid paperwork?

591
00:46:05,754 --> 00:46:08,632
Do you have a strong sense of duty?
Or are you just a do-gooder?

592
00:46:13,553 --> 00:46:16,765
Our hospital is a psychiatric clinic,

593
00:46:17,515 --> 00:46:20,227
so we have to work with another hospital
to perform surgery.

594
00:46:20,852 --> 00:46:23,521
-In your father's case--
-I told you that he's dead.

595
00:46:25,732 --> 00:46:27,901
I'm an orphan. You know that.

596
00:46:30,070 --> 00:46:31,738
But your mother is alive--

597
00:46:31,821 --> 00:46:33,740
I registered her death a long time ago.

598
00:46:35,075 --> 00:46:36,952
Do you want to hear something interesting?

599
00:46:41,206 --> 00:46:45,126
My dad's soul is dead,

600
00:46:45,710 --> 00:46:47,921
but he's physically alive like a zombie.

601
00:46:50,173 --> 00:46:51,299
As for my mom,

602
00:46:52,342 --> 00:46:54,469
she physically died many years ago.

603
00:46:56,054 --> 00:46:56,888
However,

604
00:47:01,226 --> 00:47:04,896
her soul is still alive.

605
00:47:13,238 --> 00:47:15,782
So between the two of them,
who's really dead?

606
00:47:17,450 --> 00:47:19,452
Tell me, nurse.
Which one of them is really dead?

607
00:47:21,329 --> 00:47:22,539
Your father...

608
00:47:23,832 --> 00:47:25,792
I mean, Mr. Ko Dae-hwan.

609
00:47:25,875 --> 00:47:28,837
He may end up in critical condition
if he doesn't undergo surgery this time.

610
00:47:29,337 --> 00:47:30,547
His cognitive functions--

611
00:47:30,630 --> 00:47:33,383
Hey, others will think
that you're his daughter.

612
00:47:34,134 --> 00:47:36,720
Oh, why don't we do that?
You can be Ko Dae-hwan's daughter.

613
00:47:36,803 --> 00:47:38,305
I'll be your mom's daughter.

614
00:47:38,471 --> 00:47:41,141
I'll sign this consent form
if you agree to that.

615
00:47:41,308 --> 00:47:42,142
What do you say?

616
00:48:13,381 --> 00:48:15,050
Your mom is a good cook.

617
00:48:16,009 --> 00:48:19,137
Shall I come over for some food
like the good old days?

618
00:48:22,891 --> 00:48:24,851
I see that you still don't get my jokes.

619
00:48:27,103 --> 00:48:28,396
You're no fun.

620
00:48:32,233 --> 00:48:34,277
She pisses me off.

621
00:48:35,904 --> 00:48:37,238
She's insane.

622
00:48:37,322 --> 00:48:39,324
I can't believe she writes
children's literature.

623
00:48:39,407 --> 00:48:40,992
That's bizarre.

624
00:48:41,076 --> 00:48:42,619
No, she's not "insane."

625
00:48:44,162 --> 00:48:45,622
She was just born that way.

626
00:48:45,705 --> 00:48:48,458
Goodness. Can you diagnose people
at a glance

627
00:48:48,541 --> 00:48:50,460
now that you've worked
at mental hospitals for ten years?

628
00:48:51,294 --> 00:48:52,504
Stop overreacting.

629
00:48:52,587 --> 00:48:55,048
You fool, can you please learn
to overreact a little?

630
00:48:57,550 --> 00:49:00,095
You got fired with a knife injury
because of those lunatics.

631
00:49:00,178 --> 00:49:01,554
I can't believe you just left.

632
00:49:01,638 --> 00:49:03,973
-You should've caused a scene.
-Had I done that,

633
00:49:06,351 --> 00:49:07,560
it would've felt nice,

634
00:49:09,104 --> 00:49:11,022
-but I wouldn't get my severance pay.
-Well done.

635
00:49:12,107 --> 00:49:15,318
Your brother got expelled from school,
and you got fired from work.

636
00:49:15,402 --> 00:49:17,153
You guys are two peas in a pod.

637
00:49:17,779 --> 00:49:19,489
It was about time I quit anyway.

638
00:49:25,620 --> 00:49:26,871
It's this time of the year.

639
00:49:27,956 --> 00:49:29,416
When the night breeze feels warm.

640
00:49:31,126 --> 00:49:32,127
I guess

641
00:49:34,671 --> 00:49:36,005
butterflies will appear soon.

642
00:49:40,385 --> 00:49:41,219
Right.

643
00:49:43,388 --> 00:49:46,558
How's Sang-tae? No signs yet?

644
00:49:48,309 --> 00:49:49,310
No, not yet.

645
00:49:50,311 --> 00:49:51,980
Then where should we go next?

646
00:49:54,983 --> 00:49:57,527
-Should we go to another country?
-Do you even have a passport?

647
00:49:58,027 --> 00:50:00,113
Sang-tae should learn English.

648
00:50:02,365 --> 00:50:03,241
Jae-su.

649
00:50:04,284 --> 00:50:05,743
Don't say anything to my brother.

650
00:50:05,827 --> 00:50:09,581
Gosh, you only care about your brother.
I'm sick of this.

651
00:50:10,248 --> 00:50:11,875
I'm so jealous.

652
00:50:13,168 --> 00:50:14,127
You scared me.

653
00:50:17,297 --> 00:50:19,340
What's wrong?
Did that woman also hit you in the head?

654
00:50:22,302 --> 00:50:24,596
The autograph.
I forgot to get her autograph.

655
00:50:25,096 --> 00:50:27,765
-I promised him I'd get it.
-She must've hit you hard in the head.

656
00:50:28,391 --> 00:50:29,225
What do I do, Jae-su?

657
00:50:30,351 --> 00:50:31,394
Oh, dear.

658
00:50:33,021 --> 00:50:34,898
<font color="#ffff80">AUTHOR KO MUN-YEONG'S AUTOGRAPH</font>

659
00:50:35,231 --> 00:50:36,566
<font color="#ffff80"><i>THE BOY WHO FED ON NIGHTMARES </i></font>

660
00:50:45,867 --> 00:50:48,703
Gosh, her autograph
looks like a bunch of heroglyphs.

661
00:50:49,787 --> 00:50:52,457
Hieroglyphs, not "heroglyphs."

662
00:50:54,959 --> 00:50:56,669
Hurry up. Sang-tae is waiting.

663
00:51:05,512 --> 00:51:07,138
Done. Have a look.

664
00:51:08,264 --> 00:51:10,016
Hey, look. It's very similar, isn't it?

665
00:51:18,358 --> 00:51:19,692
Nice job, Jae-su!

666
00:51:20,193 --> 00:51:22,320
Hey, quiet down.

667
00:51:25,782 --> 00:51:27,242
-Happy now?
-Yes.

668
00:51:28,201 --> 00:51:29,369
This will make Sang-tae happy.

669
00:51:32,914 --> 00:51:34,582
Don't smile like that, dude.
It disgusts me.

670
00:51:37,335 --> 00:51:39,254
A patient said the same thing to me
earlier today.

671
00:51:40,880 --> 00:51:42,215
Is my smile that annoying?

672
00:51:43,508 --> 00:51:44,342
You don't know?

673
00:51:45,843 --> 00:51:47,095
You really don't know?

674
00:51:48,263 --> 00:51:49,305
What?

675
00:51:49,639 --> 00:51:50,515
When you smile,

676
00:51:52,934 --> 00:51:54,602
you look like the Joker.

677
00:51:54,686 --> 00:51:57,730
With those sad eyes and the corners
of your lips pointing up like this.

678
00:51:59,732 --> 00:52:00,942
Look in the mirror. You'll see.

679
00:52:06,447 --> 00:52:07,323
Come on, let's go.

680
00:52:15,873 --> 00:52:17,292
Sang-tae, I'm home.

681
00:52:25,174 --> 00:52:26,134
This...

682
00:52:28,970 --> 00:52:31,097
This is fake. It's fake.

683
00:52:31,180 --> 00:52:33,766
-No, it's her real autograph. It's--
-This is fake.

684
00:52:34,267 --> 00:52:35,435
-Gosh, that's...
-This is fake.

685
00:52:35,518 --> 00:52:38,146
-Sang-tae, wait.
-This is fake.

686
00:52:38,313 --> 00:52:41,482
-Gosh, that... Goodness.
-This is fake.

687
00:52:41,566 --> 00:52:44,986
This is fake, fake, fake. It's all fake.

688
00:52:45,069 --> 00:52:47,071
You lied to me.

689
00:52:47,655 --> 00:52:50,992
-Sang-tae, I'm sorry.
-You lied to me.

690
00:52:52,118 --> 00:52:53,119
You lied to me?

691
00:52:53,202 --> 00:52:55,288
-Lying is bad.
-Sang-tae, I was too busy today that...

692
00:52:55,371 --> 00:52:57,248
Lying is bad. You lied to me?

693
00:52:57,332 --> 00:52:59,542
Even little kids know
that it's wrong to lie.

694
00:52:59,626 --> 00:53:01,586
-Shall we go to the bookstore tomorrow?
-You lied?

695
00:53:01,669 --> 00:53:04,213
-Even three-year-olds--
-Shall we get the dinosaur encyclopedia?

696
00:53:04,297 --> 00:53:06,716
-What?
-You always wanted that book.

697
00:53:08,468 --> 00:53:11,262
-Sang-tae?
-You lied?

698
00:53:12,138 --> 00:53:14,641
You lied? Why did you lie to me?

699
00:53:14,724 --> 00:53:18,603
-Lying is bad.
-Gosh, you poor thing.

700
00:53:21,105 --> 00:53:23,566
This is all Ko Mun-yeong's fault.

701
00:53:23,650 --> 00:53:26,569
I'm going to burn all these books!
What is this?

702
00:53:26,653 --> 00:53:28,613
-Why would a boy feed on nightmares?
-No!

703
00:53:28,696 --> 00:53:30,281
-No, don't.
-I'll burn all these books.

704
00:53:30,365 --> 00:53:32,075
-No, you can't!
-Look, I'll...

705
00:53:32,158 --> 00:53:33,743
-No!
-No? Why not?

706
00:53:33,826 --> 00:53:36,287
-It's mine. Don't do this.
-No, I'll burn them all.

707
00:53:36,371 --> 00:53:37,997
-<i>Hello.</i>
-Let go.

708
00:53:38,081 --> 00:53:41,376
<i>I am Lee Sang-in,
the CEO of SangSangESang Publishers,</i>

709
00:53:41,459 --> 00:53:43,753
<i>a children's book publisher.</i>

710
00:53:46,631 --> 00:53:50,677
<i>First of all,
I'd like to sincerely apologize</i>

711
00:53:50,760 --> 00:53:53,805
<i>for the unfortunate incident
between you and our author earlier today.</i>

712
00:53:56,641 --> 00:53:58,643
<i>I'd like to speak with you</i>

713
00:53:58,726 --> 00:54:01,145
<i>if you can spare a moment
out of your busy schedule.</i>

714
00:54:01,229 --> 00:54:03,106
<i>It'd be greatly appreciated</i>

715
00:54:03,189 --> 00:54:05,858
<i>if you could stop by our office tomorrow.</i>

716
00:54:07,068 --> 00:54:09,904
<i>Please don't say no.</i>

717
00:54:10,238 --> 00:54:12,907
<i>I'd really like to meet you. Please.</i>

718
00:54:22,083 --> 00:54:24,252
-<i>Please!</i>
-Why would you read children's books?

719
00:54:24,335 --> 00:54:26,921
You don't understand art.
Art is such a beautiful thing.

720
00:54:27,004 --> 00:54:29,173
What do you mean I don't understand art?
Art is...

721
00:54:29,257 --> 00:54:31,509
Naughty erotica books are what I call art.

722
00:54:31,592 --> 00:54:33,845
-This is...
-Go away. Just go home.

723
00:54:33,928 --> 00:54:36,055
-Just leave.
-Come on, Sang-tae. I like you so much.

724
00:54:40,101 --> 00:54:42,311
Of course. I knew it. Let's see.

725
00:54:44,605 --> 00:54:45,565
<i>Sure.</i>

726
00:54:46,441 --> 00:54:47,442
"Sure"?

727
00:54:47,942 --> 00:54:49,110
Gosh, that doesn't sound good.

728
00:54:49,193 --> 00:54:50,820
<i>Around 6 p.m. today
at a hospital in Seoul,</i>

729
00:54:50,903 --> 00:54:52,280
<i>-a man who was supposed</i>
-I'm getting

730
00:54:52,363 --> 00:54:55,241
-<i>to be transferred to the police</i>
-a bad feeling about this.

731
00:54:55,324 --> 00:54:57,910
<i>after attempting to take his own life
as well as his daughter's</i>

732
00:54:57,994 --> 00:55:00,997
<i>was found dead in solitary confinement.</i>

733
00:55:01,080 --> 00:55:03,124
<i>The police are investigating his death
